Task 3: Coding & Collaboration Platforms Report

Platforms Used: HackerRank, Google Forms, and Google Sheets.

Activity and Practice:
In this task, I focused on improving both my technical coding skills and collaboration abilities. For the coding part, I used HackerRank to solve the "Python If-Else" problem. This helped me understand conditional statements better and test my code against multiple automated test cases, which is essential for programming practice.

For the collaboration part, I created a "Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz" using Google Forms. I designed seven questions based on important topics such as Two-Factor Authentication (2FA), phishing awareness, and ethical use of software. I also shared the Google Form link with others to collect responses. The form was connected to Google Sheets, which automatically stored and organized the data, making it easier to analyze responses and maintain records efficiently.

Academic Benefit:
These platforms will be highly useful in my academic journey at VIT Bhopal. HackerRank will help me strengthen my coding and problem-solving skills, which are important for exams and placements. At the same time, Google Forms and Sheets will help me manage group projects, collect data, and present information in a clear and professional way. Together, these tools enhance both technical knowledge and teamwork skills.

